            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>AgentRegistry scans two directories: the main agents_dir and an optional overlay_dir managed by the Control Panel. When both have the same agent, overlay wins. This means admins can modify definitions without touching source files. reload() happens once at startup and again whenever Control Panel triggers a hot-reload. The registry exposes discovery helpers: is_routable() filters by role_kind or entry_path to find agents the router can send users to. get_default_agent_name() finds the default agent. Pydantic validation is strict — extra='forbid' means unknown fields cause an error, mode must be one of 8 known values, prompt_file must end in .md. This catches typos like 'react ' with a space or unknown modes that would silently break.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
